-- Lehman Tells Regulator It Has $1 Billion Available for Employee Benefits
-- B y   L i n d a   S a n d l e r
-- 2010-10-20T21:00:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/lehman-tells-regulator-it-has-1-billion-available-for-employee-benefits.html
Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc., the
investment bank liquidating in bankruptcy, has $1 billion
available to pay employee benefits, according to a filing with
the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  Lehman’s savings plan, started in 1984, consists mostly of
investments at “fair value,” according to today’s filing, which
reports results for 2008 and 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Linda Sandler in New York at 
 lsandler@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
